---------------------To Open Bowsers In Ruby ---------------

IMPORT :
require 'watir'
require 'selenium-webdriver'

1. We need to set path of the driver installed using selenium's 'driver path' method
Rem : Selenium in wrapped in Watir Libraries

Syntax(learn by heart):

*> SET-PATH = Selenium::WebDriver::Chrome/Firefox.driver_path="give_path"


2. Create the object of the 'Browser' class

*> obj = Watir::Browser.new (:chrome/firefox)

